<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="Blue-Sensitive" class="currentChild" href="Blue-Sensitive">Blue-Sensitive</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
A type of photographic film which is only sensitive to light in the <a title="Blue" href="Blue">blue</a> portion of the <a title="Visible Spectrum" href="Visible_Spectrum">visible spectrum</a> (or, in other words, light having a wavelength between 450 and 500 <a title="Nanometer" href="Nanometer">nanometer</a>s) and in the <a title="Ultraviolet" href="Ultraviolet">ultraviolet</a> portion of the spectrum. Also known as <a title="Color Blind" href="Color_Blind">color blind</a> film, blue-sensitive film—unlike <a title="Orthochromatic" href="Orthochromatic">orthochromatic</a> and <a title="Panchromatic" href="Panchromatic">panchromatic</a> films—can be used somewhat safely outside a darkroom, and is often used for photoimaging utilizing ultraviolet light. 
</p>
